To factor the quadratic in \(m\),

We look for two numbers whose product is \(-56\) (the constant term) and whose sum is \(+1\) (the coefficient of \(m\)).  Those numbers are \(+8\) and \(-7\).  Hence

\(m^{2} + m\,n - 56\,n^{2}
= m^{2} + (8n - 7n)\,m - 56n^{2}
= (m + 8n)(m - 7n).\)
